Recovery Time Objective (RTO) defines how quickly systems must be restored after an outage.

Recovery Point Objective (RPO) defines how much data loss is acceptable.

Example:

| Application        | RTO        | RPO        |
| ------------------ | ---------- | ---------- |
| Online Banking     | 15 minutes | 1 minute   |
| Corporate Email    | 2 hours    | 30 minutes |
| Internal HR Portal | 8 hours    | 2 hours    |

A real-life use case is financial organizations requiring extremely low RPO values.

Understanding RTO and RPO helps organizations design suitable disaster recovery strategies.
